Package it.polimi.ingsw.client.GUI.sceneHandlers

Class GamePhaseHandler

java.lang.Object
it.polimi.ingsw.client.GUI.sceneHandlers.PhaseHandler
it.polimi.ingsw.client.GUI.sceneHandlers.GamePhaseHandler
public class GamePhaseHandler
extends PhaseHandler
This class is the controller for all the JavaFX scenes used during the actual game phase.

      setScene in class PhaseHandler
      Parameters:

      Returns:
      true if the scene has been set correctly, false if GamePhaseHandler is not a controller for that scene

    • initiateBoard

      public void initiateBoard()
      Initiate the main board upon starting the game and then starts to listen for player's input.
      • Set the leaders held by the player;
      • Set the initial warehouse;
      • Set the market and the available Development cards;
      • Set the preview of the enemies;
      • Initiate the player's Faith Track

    • updateBoard

      public void updateBoard()
      Initiate the main board upon starting the game and then starts to listen for player's input.
      • Update the leaders held by the player;
      • Update warehouse;
      • Set the market and the available Development cards;
      • Update the preview of the enemies;
      • Update the player's Faith Track
      • Update the pope passes status
      • Update the Development cards status

    • observePlayerActions

      public void observePlayerActions()
      Set all the behaviors in response to a player input from the main board.

      Furthermore, it informs the players about their turn through the message box.

    • setMarket

      public void setMarket()
      Fill the market region with the current resources as set in ClientController

    • sendErrorToMsgBoard

      public void sendErrorToMsgBoard​(java.lang.String message)
      It will show the error message to the player through the Message Box. The text will turn red.
      Parameters:
      message - error message that has to be displayed in the Message Box

    • setActionToken

      public void setActionToken​(ActionToken act)
      It display the image of the token act on the right side of the player's board.
      Parameters:
      act - the Action Token drawn during the last Lorenzo's turn

    • chooseStoragePopUp

      public void chooseStoragePopUp​(java.util.List<Resource> selectedRes, boolean isBadStorageRequest, boolean isRearrangeRequest)
      It will open the pop-up that allows the player to place the resources in selectedRes into the Warehouse's shelves.
      Parameters:
      selectedRes - the list of resources that needs to be stored by the player
      isBadStorageRequest - true if a BadStorageException has been thrown by the server sending a BAD_STORAGE_REQUEST and the resources need to be rearranged again
      isRearrangeRequest - true if the player wants to rearrange the resources he/she already has in the Warehouse

    • resetStoragePopUp

      public void resetStoragePopUp()

    • setProductionCards

      public void setProductionCards()
      Place all the still available Development cards to purchase in the grid. The cards are chosen as the version represented in the ClientController.

      The grid is divided into 12 decks, each of 4 cards. Once a deck is empty, it replaces the image with a back card image.

    • sendMsgPopUp

      public void sendMsgPopUp​(java.lang.String msg)
      Display the message in a pop-up.
      Parameters:
      msg - the message to be displayed

    • sendMsgPopUp

      public void sendMsgPopUp​(java.lang.String msg1, java.lang.String msg2)
      Display the messages for Lorenzo's actions in a pop-up.
      Parameters:
      msg1 - the main message
      msg2 - the additional information to place under msg1

    • displayWinner

      public void displayWinner​(java.lang.String winner)
      Change the scene displayed on the stage showing if the player has won or the "defeat" scene informing who has won the match.
      Parameters:
      winner - the name of the winner of the game
